new venezuela debt interest rate goe into effect the new interest rate of 7/8 pct over libor on venezuelan public sector debt payment goe into effect today , financ minist manuel azpurua said . azpurua told report yesterday the reduct from the previou margin of 1-1/8 pct abov libor will save the countri some 50 mln dollar in debt servic . the new rate is among chang agre last month to the 20.3 billion dlr public sector debt reschedul . under the new agreement , venezula wa also abl to extend the term from 12 to 14 year and to lower debt payment in the 1987-89 period by 64 pct . azpurua said that accord to the agreement , the new interest rate will be retroact to april 1 , provid the accord is approv befor octob 1. he told report the term sheet detail the chang in the reschedul ha alreadi been endors by the 13-member debt steer committe and is now be sent to the country' 460 creditor bank for their approv . the new agreement replac a reschedul accord sign in februari 1986 , which venezuela ask to revis to reflect a 45 pct drop in oil revenu .